node.text: No one wants to protect environment truly.. Just need protect from others human but not from environment
No one wants to protect environment truly.. Just need protect from others human but not from environment

Despite threats to human existence from #climatechange, #biodiversity loss and a #pandemic that’s devastating economies and paralysing societies, countries still spend recklessly on destructive weapons for wars they will never fight. Cross-border invasions and civil wars are in decline, but political instability and unrest is rising across many regions, including North and South America, Africa and Asia. In the past decade, the number of riots and anti-government demonstrations has more than doubled globally
More than 96 of the world’s countries recorded a violent demonstration in 2019 as citizens protested against racial injustice, police brutality, corruption and economic decline. Weapons don’t get at the root causes of instability — poor governance, lack of food, few jobs, poor education provision and threats to safety. The might of the military does not make the world more peaceful.

#ActOnClimate #LeadOnClimate #MoveTheDate #youthstrike4climate #FridaysforFuture

node.text:
Kerja Keras, Kerja Ikhlas, Sempurnakan Dengan Zakat Penghasilan

Assalamu'alaikum warahmatullahi wabarakatuh 

Bapak/Ibu yang dimuliakan Allah 

Sahabat Dermawan, yuk segera alokasikan gaji yang kita dapat untuk membayar zakat. Karena menunaikan zakat telah menjadi kewajiban yang harus kita lakukan setelah mendapatkan gaji atau penghasilan.

_Insha Allah kita tak perlu khawatir, Allah telah menjamin harta yang dikeluarkan di jalan Allah, akan diganjar berlipat ganda sekaligus mampu membersihkan jiwa dan harta kita._

Sebaliknya, orang yang ENGGAN MEMBAYAR zakat karena kikir atau membayarnya namun tidak sesuai kewajibannya, maka ia telah berbuat zhalim.

Sebagaimana Firman Allah Ta’ala, yang artinya: _"Dan orang-orang yang menyimpan emas dan perak dan tidak menafkahkannya pada jalan Allah, maka beritahukanlah kepada mereka, (bahwa mereka akan mendapat) siksa yang pedih." (QS. At-Taubah: 34)._

Sahabat Dermawan yang dirahmati Allah, mari segerakan membayar zakat. Jangan sampai harta yang kita miliki habis begitu saja tanpa sampai kepada mereka yang berhak.

_Bismillah,_ mari salurkan zakat dan sedekah terbaik bersama Global Zakat-ACT melalui tautan https://depok.indonesiadermawan.id/ZakatPenghasilan

Atau melalui nomor rekening
BNI Syariah 990000251
Atas nama Yayasan Global Zakat

_Jazaakumullah Khairan Sahabat Dermawan. Dengan sedekah, kian tumbuhkan berkah. Dengan Zakat, mari kita selamatkan Ummat._

Aksi Cepat Tanggap (ACT)
🏢 Jln. Ir. H.Juanda No.20 Kemiri Muka Kota Depok
☎ 021-77807805

node.text:
Join us for a #RequiemForJustice, an International Online Rally of Artists, Thinkers, and Activists Against Injustice on August 28, 29 and 30 at 10:30pm IST  17:00 GMT

We are participating with 7 video features from India, featuring Harsh Mander, Arundhati Roy, T M Krishna, Mohit Chauhan, Aamir Aziz and Tishani Doshi and including "Stranded" - a documentary on India's harsh lockdown. 

These will premiere online at 10:30pm on Saturday, 29 August, 2020. Tishani Doshi's poetry reading is on Friday, 28 Aug.

The rest of the 3 day program features artists from Afghanistan, Ghana, Columbia, Lebanon, UK, USA, Libya, Nigeria, Uzbekistan, Brazil, Spain and more.
The Requiem for Justice programme will stream on the FB pages of  @karwanemohabbat @equitystudies @landscapeofhope_ @actforhope on Youtube and Facebook.

Herkese günaydın,
Son 3 gündür yaşadıklarımı anlatacağım #zayiflayannngelinicinidokuyor olacak biraz ❤
Temmuz ortalarında bacak içlerimde ve arkalarında #hidradenitissuppurativa ataklarım başlamıştı, oldukça ağrılı bir süreç, yaklaşık 18 yıldır belli dönemlerde benimle olan bir durum olduğu için ve ağrı eşiğim biraz yüksek olduğundan günlük hayatıma devam edebiliyordum fakat Ağustosun 5 gibi dayanılmaz bir hal aldı ve dokrora gittim 7 günlük #antibiyotik tedavisine başladık, kontrolde ise atağın devam etmesi nedeniyle 5 gün daha ilaca devam ettik. (ilerleyen günlerde farklı bir tedavi yontemi olabilir)
Bildiginiz gibi yagdan yogunluklu kg. verdigim icin regl duzensizliklerim vardi. 5 ay 3 gun ardindan regl olmustum ve sonrasinda hemen duzene girmesini beklemiyordum ama ya yine aylarca regl olamam diye cok korkuyordum. Neyseki bu sefer sadece 25 gunluk aradan sonra regl ile birbirimize kavustuk, offf ama nasil bir agri nasil bir kaos durumla kavuştuk anlatamam 🙈 
Regl olmadan 2 gun once cam acik kalmis ve Bursada havalar serinledigi icin sabaha karsi usuyerek uyandim.
Bu 3 ana etken benim minnoş bedenimi öyle bir sarstı ki 22 Ağustos öğleden sonra ateşim 37.8 i gördü #parol le yaklaşık 6-7 saatte 36.8 e indirebildik, 23 Ağustos 3 de ablamın "yanıyorsun, hemen acile gidelim" demesi ile uyandım, ama adım ataçak mecalim yoktu.
Acile 38.8 ateşle giriş yaptık, #covit19 un belirtilerinin bir çoğu yoktu çok şükür fakat vucudum da inanılmaz ağrıyordu (bu ağrı bir önceki regl döneminde de olmuştu) akciğer filmi çekildi, kan tahlili yapıldı, bana hemen serum takıldı. Aradan bir kaç saat geçti çok şükür ki ateşim 38 e düştü, film ve tahlil sonuçlarımı değerlendirmek için doktorla bir araya geldik, akciğer filmimin temiz çıktığını, kan değerlerimin bir çoğunun referans değer aralığında olduğunu sadece d-dimer imin yüksek olduğunu, ateşle şikayeti ile giriş yaptığımız içinde #covit19 testi yaptıracağını söyledi. 
O an kendimin hasta olmasından ziyade, sevdiklerime bunu bulaştıracak olabilme ihtimali beni çok üzdü, tabi deyip testi verdim, sonucun en geç 48 saat içinde e-nabıza düşeceğini iletti. Sonuç çıkana kadar izole olmamı, pozitif olma durumunda ise (devmi yorumlrda)

node.text:
Sommer, Sonne und Sorglosigkeit? Leider ist das in Zeiten von Corona nicht ganz so möglich, wie es in den letzten Jahren der Fall war. Denn die Infektionszahlen steigen in Deutschland wieder an. 😷🤒

Einige Wissenschaftler sprechen sogar vom Beginn einer zweiten Welle. Daher ist es wichtig, sich weiterhin an die verordneten Maßnahmen zu halten. Wir alle können unseren Teil dazu beitragen, die Corona-Pandemie weitestgehend einzudämmen.

Auf folgende Maßnahmen sollten wir achten:

✅ Genug Abstand halten: Achtet auf einen Mindestabstand von mindestens 1,5 Meter zu anderen Personen.

✅ Wenn ihr Krankheitszeichen wie Husten, Schnupfen oder Fieber habt, solltet ihr zu Hause bleiben und gegebenenfalls euren Hausarzt telefonisch kontaktieren.

✅ Verzichtet auf das Händeschütteln oder Umarmen, wenn ihr einen anderen Menschen begrüßen oder verabschieden wollt.

✅ Niest oder hustet in die Armbeuge oder in ein Taschentuch. Das Taschentuch solltet ihr anschließend entsorgen.

✅ Vermeidet es, mit den Händen den Mund, die Augen oder die Nase zu berühren.

✅ Tragt eine Mund-Nasen-Bedeckung, um andere zu schützen. Ein Mundschutz muss an Orten getragen werden, an denen es vorgeschrieben ist. Bleibt daher über die aktuellen Bestimmungen informiert. Im Moment müssen Atemschutzmasken in Geschäften und im öffentlichen Nahverkehr getragen werden.

✅ Zusätzlich empfiehlt es sich, eine Mund-Nasen-Bedeckung zu tragen, wenn der Mindestabstand von 1,5 Meter nicht eingehalten werden kann.

node.text:
let me put things into context for you...

if i can be honest i don’t post things to get likes. i do it so i can share. but i also know things gotta be put into context. so back in 2015 a white man by the name of Dylan Roof walked into a church, shot and murdered 9 black people. Dylan was eventually found and arrested but before being taken into custody, officers stopped off at a fast food restaurant to get him something to eat because...he was hungry. 

two days ago a black man by the name of Jacob Blake tried to break up a fight between two women, where cops tried to apprehend him, and eventually shot him 7 times in the back while he was trying get back into his car, with his three young boys still in the car.  also Jacob was unarmed.  and even tho he survived, he’s now paralyzed and his 3 boys will forever be scarred and traumatized by the image of seeing their father nearly murdered. again, i don’t post things for likes, i do it so i can share. but tell me...is that enough context for you??? ✊🏻✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿 #howmanymore #justiceforJacobBlake

The arrival of Gauri in one’s home represents health, wealth and prosperity. An avatar of Parvati, the Gauri is envisioned as the Goddess of forest, so one can see her surroundings all bedecked with flowers and shrubs, so she is depicted standing in a lotus pond or even in a grand avatar.

Myths say that a certain unpleasant incident took place in her life which made her retreat to the forests greens for days together. Amidst nature, she performed a most severe course of austerities. She focused to develop Her spiritual powers. This caught the attention of Lord Brahma. He decided to grant Her one wish. The wish of eternal beauty and grace so that she may fill her life with love of her partner, nurturing of her children and prosperity of a healthy and happy life.

Prima Donna – Diviya Aggarwal wishes everyone a blessed Gauri-puja and urges all to think of the current situation as a test like the one Goddess Gauri passed so that we too may be granted the wishes we want.

node.text:
STAY HOME IF SICK - GET TESTED.⁠
⁠
As the number of COVID-19 cases in NSW starts to rise again, it is important to increase testing to ensure any new cases or outbreaks are identified and managed rapidly. To help with this, it is vitally important that people who are feeling unwell stay home and get tested - even if they have been tested before.⁠
⁠
@nswhealth recommends testing for anyone that has #covid_19 symptoms, including: ⁠
🤒 fever;⁠
🤒 cough;⁠
🤒 sore/scratchy/tickly throat;⁠
🤒 shortness of breath;⁠
🤒 loss of smell;⁠
🤒 loss of taste;⁠
🤒 runny nose;⁠
🤒 joint pains;⁠
🤒 muscle pains;⁠
🤒 diarrhoea;⁠
🤒 nausea/vomiting; or⁠
🤒 loss of appetite.⁠
⁠
Testing is especially important for:⁠
🤒 anyone who lives or works in a high-risk setting, including healthcare facilities, aged care and other residential facilities, schools, prisons, and other closed settings;⁠
🤒Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people;⁠
🤒people who are close contacts of a confirmed case or who have returned from overseas in the last 14 days;⁠
🤒anyone admitted to hospital; and⁠
🤒people who reside in areas for increased testing and surveillance.⁠
⁠
People without symptoms do not require testing, except in special circumstances.⁠
⁠
If you are unwell, please call the practice on 02 4252 5200 to arrange testing.⁠
⁠
@illawarrafamilymedicalcentre, your health matters to us.⁠
⁠
⁠

node.text:
ΤΕΣΤ ΓΙΑ COVID-19 ΣΤΑ ΠΑΙΔΙΑ !

Το πότε ένα παιδί θα κάνει τεστ για τον Κορονοϊό έγκειται στην κρίση του θεράποντος παιδιάτρου.

Η αλήθεια είναι ότι δεν έχουμε πάντα τη δυνατότητα να στείλουμε το παιδί για μοριακό τεστ. Τα νοσοκομεία εξυπηρετούν ένα μεγάλο όγκο ασθενών και εκτελούν τους ελέγχους βάσει των οδηγιών του ΕΟΔΥ. Τα ιδιωτικά εργαστήρια από την άλλη είναι ακόμα πολύ λίγα για να καλύψουν όλο το πληθυσμό. Σημαντικό είναι να αναφέρουμε και το υψηλό κόστος καθώς το τεστ δεν καλύπτεται από τον ΕΟΠΥΥ.

Στον πίνακα έχουμε προσπαθήσει να συγκεντρώσουμε τις περιπτώσεις όπου το τεστ για covid-19 στα παιδιά κρίνεται απολύτως απαραίτητο.

Υπάρχουν στοιχεία από το ιστορικό που θα μας βοηθήσουν να αποφασίσουμε το ποια παιδιά θα πρέπει να κάνουν το τεστ :

Για παράδειγμα αν πρόκειται για μεγάλο παιδί που μπορεί να έχει επαφές με άλλους τότε αυτό είναι ένα ύποπτο στοιχείο.
 
Αν πρόκειται για μικρότερο που βρίσκεται διαρκώς με τους γονείς του, τότε αν κάποιος από τους μεγάλους έχει πυρετό η υποψία για covid γίνεται μεγαλύτερη, αφού το μικρότερο παιδί συνήθως θα κολλήσει από το οικογενειακό του περιβάλλον.

Στοιχεία όπως το αν η περιοχή έχει πολλά κρούσματα ή αν ταξίδεψαν πρόσφατα με μαζικό μέσο μεταφοράς έχουν επίσης την αξία τους.
 
Γενικά θα προσπαθήσουμε να αποκλείσουμε κάποια επαφή με κρούσμα.

Παρ' όλα αυτά ο μόνος σίγουρος τρόπος για να αποκλείσουμε ή να επιβεβαιώσουμε covid είναι το μοριακό τεστ. Ωστόσο και αυτό αν γίνει πολύ νωρίς μπορεί να βγει αρνητικό λόγω χαμηλού ιϊκού φορτίου και μπορεί να χρειαστεί και δεύτερο.

node.text:
BAI Intelligence is a 'Game-changer' according to Tyler Larson, the General Manager of Athletic Society. node.text:
The Modi Government's plan to sell the loss-making national carrier Air India has hit another hurdle. The government has extended the deadline for interested bidders to place their bids for Air India by two more months to October 30 as against the previous deadline of August 31. 

The Department of Investment and Public Asset Management (DIPAM) said the deadline has been extended in view of the "request received from the interested bidders in view of the prevailing situation arising out of COVID-19". This is the fourth extension given by the government for putting in bids for the national carrier.

Officers sprayed disinfectant around the Griya Yasa housing area, Wanasari Village, Cibitung District, Bekasi Regency, West Java on Wednesday morning (26/08). Oki, one of the volunteers said that the spraying was carried out after the Humanitarian Organization Lingkar Peduli and the Rela Baik Community received a report from residents that there was 1 positive patient in Griya Yasa Housing, responding to the report, the volunteers immediately sprayed disinfectant to sterilize the environment around the patient's house.

Seen 👀 our Schwarz COVID-19 Marshals at our inspections and auctions lately? 

Due to a large increase of attendees at our open homes, we felt it was super important to have a hygiene marshal as part of our COVID-19 Safety Plan!

The marshal is responsible for monitoring the inspection and ensure all safety measures are in place. Our safety plan includes, a complimentary Schwarz sanitiser bottle, cleaning prior to open, masks, record keeping and maintaining social distancing. 

Let's all do our part to keep each other safe and Live, Well 💕

【パースエクスプレス・ウェブサイト】
.
【新型コロナウイルス関連】「前島イズム」でお馴染みの前島一貴さんが体操選手の海外活動をサポート！
.
パースエクスプレスマガジンの人気連載コーナー「前島イズム 継続の“エクササイズ”」でお馴染みの前島一貴さんが、新型コロナウイルスの影響により日本へ帰国されました。パースに残された私たちにとっては惜しまれつつの日本帰国となってしまいましたが、前島さんは帰国当日から積極的に自身の掲げた使命に向かって突き進んでいるようです。
.
パースエクスプレス・ウェブサイトでは、その前島さんに日本への帰国の経緯や帰国後の活動、体操選手の海外活動サポート事業の立ち上げについて、また「日本初男子オンライン体操競技イベント」開催など3月以降急変されたご自身の生活やお仕事についてお話を伺っています。
.

node.text:
Vendo mascaras personalizadas! São 09 modelos, todos produzidos em espuma vinílica acetinada de 5mm (10mm nas áreas sobrepostas), com dupla camada sobreposta de tecido-não-tecido nas janelas de respiração, cujo microfibrilas dispostas em forma aleatória garantem maior capacidade de filtragem. Todos os modelos, com exceção da WARRIOR, possuem elasticos para uso na parte superior da nuca e pescoço, evitando o desconforto dos elásticos convencionais presos a orelha. Com um simples nó, você pode regular o elástico para melhor ajuste ao seu rosto. O modelo WARRIOR é preso por velcro! Usa óculos? As máscaras possuem design inteligente que se acomodam perfeitamente as curvas do rosto, impedindo que o ar quente suba e embace suas lentes. Isso mesmo, suas lentes não embaçam! Todas as mascaras são laváveis e também higienizáveis por álcool pulverizado.

Cores: Disponível nas cores CINZA e PRETO conforme imagens ilustrativas (podendo inverter o padrão ou pintar integralmente em uma única cor).

Por um valor simbólico adicional de R$ 5,00 ao valor original, qualquer máscara pode ser adaptada ao velcro.

Por um valor simbólico adicional de R$ 10,00 ao valor original, pode ser realizado pintura com Esmalte Sintético nas cores Branco, Rubro, Azul  e Rosa.

node.text: @hi_pierre2.0 I AGREE  ABOUT THE SECOND HAND SMOKE.  I AGREE  ABOUT  THE CANCER.  HOWEVER  I DON'T  AGREE  WHEN YOU SAY MASK DON'T  WORK.! INSWED THEY DO.  THATS THE UNFORTUNATE THING ABOUT SCIENCE .  MOST OF THE INFORMATION  AT FIRST  ARE THEORIZED  ESPECIALLY  DEALING WITH CORONAVIRUS DISEASE 2019 ( COVID19)  ITS A NEW STRAIN  AND THE PRESIDENT  HAS PRESSERIZED THE CDC AND THE DOCTORS  TO SAY SOMETHING  FAST.  SAY ANYTHING  BUT COME UP WITH THE REMEDY IMMEDIATELY  BECAUSE  HIS REELECTION  DEPENDS ON A MEDICATION  OR VACCINE.  SO YES, THE MORE THE SCIENTISTS  LEARN ABOUT THIS UNKNOWN  PREDITORIAL  ENTITY  THE DATA MABE  DIFFERENT FROM YESTERDAY.  THATS HOW RESEARCH  AND SCIENCE  WORKS.  THE INFORMATION  IS MERCURIAL.  IM A REGISTERED NURSE  AND I KNOW  ABOUT  PEOPLE  DIEING  FROM BRONCHIOGENIC CARCINOMA.  I  ALSO NOW HOW THE MASK ABSOLUTELY IS A PROTECTIVE  EQUIPMENT  INDIVIDUALS  SHOULD  ABSOLUTELY  WEAR!  NO, THEY ARE ALL NOT EQUAL, THAT DEPENDS  ON YOUR SUPPLIER.  WEARING A MASK PROTECTS OTHER INDIVIDUALS FROM THE WEARER BECAUSE.  YOU MAYBE  ASYMPTOMATIC  AND NOT FEEL  LIKE  WEARING  A  MASK !  YOU PROTECT  YOUR ELDERLY GRAND PARENTS  OR THAT ELDERLY PERSON IN THE ELEVATOR OR STANDING BEHIND YOU IN THE GROCERY STORE.  HAVING  WORKED IN ICU FOR 48 YRS.  IV SEEN DEATH FAR TO MANY  TO COUNT, YET I CAN RECALL EVERY ONE OF THEM AND SO MANY  SAID THEY WISHED  THEY HAD NEVER  PICKED UP A CIGARETTE. @lolonana1847 I understand where @hi_pierre2.0 is coming from. I am in New Zealand at the moment. During the 1st wave of Covid19 we were told not to wear masks as they aren't effective in preventing the disease. We managed to get rid of the disease all together. Now the second wave has come, the professionals have changed their minds, maybe due to the fact that some spread the disease before they knew they had it. Now people must wear a mask on public transport, and they suggest that people wear masks or face coverings such as a scarf etc to cover their faces when they leave their homes until it is under control again. Depending on the medical professionals, advice will continue to change. They are pushing social distancing and washing hands as that is the cheapest, more effective way to prevent the disease. But  this may change, just like the disease mutated itself. Us stroke survivors have to be extra vigilant as it has been known to cause blot clots, more so in younger people.

node.text:
It's  Tuesday so that means it's time to share  those testimonies. We overcome by the blood of the Lamb and the words of our what?!! TESTIMONIES!! YES! 

Don't  keep God's  goodness and faithful to yourself let the world know how great our God is. I know Yahweh  has definitely brought us through some things the year so use the post to inspire  others to keep trusting and pushing towards the mark of the high calling. 

We all have something to testify about. So don't be shy, just the fact that we are all still here today is a testimony not infected by covid-19 is another testimony . Still have income whether it's from employment or unemployment is a testimony,  people are finding their gifts/purpose  is a testimony,  folks are opening businesses, purchasing  land, buying houses in the times of this pandemic now that should make you shout cause God is still making a way during the storm.

So again, let's overcome by the words of our testimonies today, and help increase someone  faith cause if he did it for you, he will definitely do it for others he has no respect  of person. He's always good and faithful to those who seek him. 

🚨I always go first, so this time I still open up the opportunity for someone else to go first 🙂 now comment below and share the goodness of our father 

 Keep in mind he will supply all your needs according to his riches and glory!! Praise God. Share your testimony below we are waiting and even if you didnt see this post on a tuesday you can still share his goodness all week long in the comment section below
He better than good to us💙

node.text: Hey Dash! Love the mask! I was actually just translating something that said a mask with mixed materials is more effective. Apparently if you have one layer of cotton and one of silk it's about 90% effective. Who knew?
Cute!! Hope you are doing well!

Hey Dash! Love the mask! I was actually just translating something that said a mask with mixed materials is more effective. Apparently if you have one layer of cotton and one of silk it's about 90% effective. Who knew?
Cute!! Hope you are doing well!

It's neat one of the ways people have embraced mask-wearing is to decorate and customize their #facecovering .
That said, it is also important to keep in mind the purpose of the mask: to #prevent spread of #infection !! Some materials are better than others for this. This is probably the only time you will ever see me say that silk is not going to make something better.  My #diy masks are two layers of 100% #cotton with a non-woven interface interposed btwn them.  As you can see, I've started making matching headbands as well!

An observational multi-center study, coordinated by the I.R.C.C.S. Neuromed, with the participation of 33 #Italian hospitals, shows that the risk of death is 30% lower for #coronavirus patients treated with #hydroxychloroquine

An Italian observational study contributes to the ongoing debate regarding the use of hydroxychloroquine in the current #pandemic. The research, conducted on 3,451 patients treated in 33 hospitals throughout the Italian territory (list of participating centers attached), shows that the use of this drug reduces by 30% the risk of death in hospitalized patients affected by #Covid19.

Published in the European Journal of Internal Medicine, the study was coordinated by the Department of Epidemiology and Prevention of the I.R.C.C.S. Neuromed, Pozzilli, in collaboration with #MediterraneaCardiocentro, #Naples, and the #UniversityofPisa, with the participation of 33 hospitals forming the CORIST collaboration (#COvid-19 RISk and Treatments). Researchers analysed data regarding current and previous diseases, therapies followed before the infection and drugs administered in the hospital specifically for the treatment of COVID-19. All this information was compared with the evolution and the final in-hospital outcome of the infection.

“We observed – explains Augusto Di Castelnuovo, epidemiologist at the Neuromed Department of Epidemiology and Prevention, currently at Mediterranea Cardiocentro in Naples – that patients treated with hydroxychloroquine had a 30% lower in-hospital mortality rate compared to those not receiving this treatment. Our data were subjected to extremely rigorous statistical analysis, taking into account all the variables and possible confounding factors that could come into play. The drug efficacy was evaluated in various subgroups of patients. The positive results of hydroxychloroquine treatment remained unchanged, especially in those patients showing a more evident inflammatory state at the moment of admission to hospital”.

🖐🏾More in comments👇🏾

In America, it estimated that if America followed through with the herd immunity concept that roughly
3 MILLION 
Americans would die out of a population of 329 million people.

I’d like to share my view on this, hope that’s ok...I have said all along that I am not afraid of the virus. The reason being is I believe our bodies are powerful and effective at fighting viruses. I prefer to live trusting my body rather than in the extreme fear that is being repeated over and over from the Gov and media. This doesn’t mean that I don’t care for the elderly or those not healthy, it just means that I am not afraid. I have made extreme sacrifices for nearly half a year for those who are vulnerable. What I am afraid of is the huge psychological toll the lockdowns are having on people. I feel these will have a bigger toll than the virus 💚

What I am afraid of is the huge psychological toll the lockdowns are having on people. I feel these will have a bigger toll than the virus 💚

This is the logical extension of 'survival of the fittest'. It's a really fucked up concept when applied to humanity. No place for compassion. No  place for kindness. The ultimate individualist doctrine. Ayn Rand would be proud....😢😢😢😢😢
.
.
.

node.text: Where is this occurring exactly?? Inquiring minds want to know.
Where is this occurring exactly?? Inquiring minds want to know.

This article makes me too angry for words!!!
.
Women giving birth are not allowed their partners and or their doulas, thus leading to more dangerous interventions.
.
Women giving birth are forced to wear masks throughout their labor.  Having labored for more than 30 hours with my first born, I can tell you with certainty that such a measure is pure torture and will lead to more medical interventions.  This is Dr. Mengele style medical Tyranny!
.
Under the guise of this virus, women are forced to deliver while laying on their backs, which is the most difficult way to give birth.  This has absolutely no medical basis and it’s merely yet another abuse inflicted on a woman while she is most vulnerable and will undoubtedly lead to more dangerous medical interventions (like episiotomy).
.
But if all these abuses are not enough, if the totally worthless covid test comes back positive, the new mother is separated from her newborn baby.  This will have life long repercussions and it is the most cruel punishment for both mother and baby.  The first few hours after the birth are extraordinarily important to produce the bonding between mother and baby.  Hormones adjust, colostrum is triggered,  providing the baby with life saving immunity. 
.
These monsters, these pseudo-humans who mandate these inhumane policies need to be tarred and feathered, for they are ruining lives!
.
I gave birth at home to both of my children.  Giving birth in American Hospitals was already a nightmarish experience.  Terms like “Birth Rape” describe what happens to women there, but giving birth there in the Age of Covid is pure torture!  Any woman in her right mind would be well advised to consider birthing at home... 
.

location.address_json: {"street_address": "Campo della Salute", "zip_code": "30123", "city_name": "Venice, Italy", "region_name": "", "country_code": "IT", "exact_city_match": false, "exact_region_match": false, "exact_country_match": false}

node.text:
At the Basilica di Santa Maria della Salute (Saint Mary of Health) in Venice. An emblematic church built as a plea to God to end the ruthless plague that killed nearly a third of the Venetian population. 

I remember thinking how incredibly terrifying and devastating it must have been to live in the midst of so much death and uncertainty.

I never imagined that we would find ourselves in the middle of a pandemic in our lifetime. I can’t help but to appreciate more the history of this church and the people of Venice, drawing parallels with the mask wearing then and now to prevent contagion.

Fortunately for us, our plea is to science with the hope of a vaccine that will help us return to normal with a richer appreciation for life.
-
August 2018 Photos
-

node.text:
“Following my heart to save yours.” I put this cute li’l quote into a design for our class shirt in 2015. 💙
Now in 2020, I feel the more applicable quote is “Risking my life to save yours.” Everyday I go to work, I’m putting my life at risk. I’ve kept myself from visiting family for fear of being a carrier for the virus. The anxiety of it all is so heavy that I can’t keep myself from crying sometimes. This last month in particular has been an emotional rollercoaster. I’ve had two patients, one being my clinic patient, die in the ICU. I witnessed death... but I also witnessed new life. I delivered two babies and performed their newborn exams. I’ve cared for pediatric patients, too. I even discharged a patient who been hospitalized for 3 months into the arms of his loving family. Full spectrum, baby!👩🏻‍⚕️
Although some days are extremely difficult, I still am able to find joy - joy that I am granted this opportunity learn to care for people. 💫

@jerrydalemcfadden and where we were born & partially raised!  Oh we miss Europe. Trust me on that one! You can rub it in. Although the recent news about Spain saddens me. ❤️💋 love you dale
I won’t rub it in about the country I live in.
I won’t rub it in about the country I live in.
@jerrydalemcfadden and where we were born & partially raised!  Oh we miss Europe. Trust me on that one! You can rub it in. Although the recent news about Spain saddens me. ❤️💋 love you dale

Hands up who’s following the science, wearing face masks, social distancing, sheltering in place(in our country or others where COVID is not under control?) Every day I see people doing none of that, just spreading anything they might have. What are they thinking? We need leadership and discipline. 7 years ago, my passion for fashion could be enjoyed daily. Ha, not even hardly ever. I see lots of people that are and lots that are not. It makes me angry. The sooner we get both we will see a light at this end of this tragic tunnel. It’s almost September and we’ve been living through this and will be for some time to come. I love being at home, I can easily do all of it. I can’t easily watch all the suffering and death. It renews my faith in humankind all the people who I do see doing it all.  The other people and I see a large % acting like nothing’s going on, are selfish idiots who have no concerns for others. I’ll stop there. Get lost now. Don’t stand so close to me. I’m one of the lucky ones still. #covid_19 #socialdistancing #facemask #followthescience #drfauci #pandemic #willlifeeverbethesame #millionslostjobs #economycrisis #foodbanks #evictions #homeless #nostimuluschecks I care. About the world. This isn’t the country my parents escaped to come here for freedom.

.

When Melania Trump addresses the Republican convention from the White House, it will be the most that many Americans have seen of their first lady since the beginning of the coronavirus pandemic. 

Out of the public view for much of the year, Mrs. Trump will step into the spotlight to argue for a second term for her husband. 

Her message will be uplifting and positive, said Stephanie Grisham, the first lady’s spokesperson. “It reflects on her time as first lady and some of her favorite moments. There’s a couple of moments in there that I think will be really key,” Grisham said. “And then it’s really, really forward-looking and to not only what she wants to do in the next four years, but why she thinks the president is best for our country.” 

Just like Trump has upended norms of the presidency, Melania Trump has altered what it means to be a modern first lady, from continuing to live in New York City in the administration's opening months to forcing the ouster of a deputy national security adviser. 

Not since Nancy Reagan has any first lady asserted herself so publicly in West Wing personnel matters. Visit the link in our bio for the latest updates on night two of the RNC. (Photo credit: J. Scott Applewhite/AP)

I began this piece at the start of the pandemic in the New York, when it was the epicenter of the pandemic. My wife was on the front lines at a hospital in New York and it felt like every day she was walking into a storm. Every day was uncertain and I channeled those feelings into this music, tentatively titled “The Storm”. Sharing a short excerpt from this unfinished piece, dedicated to the frontline workers around the world working hard to fight this virus.

node.text: En este pequeño taller se producen más de diez ataúdes por día. Es una carpintería del municipio de San Pedro Perulapán, en el departamento de Cuscatlán, que trabaja como nunca antes para cubrir la demanda que ha generado la pandemia de covid-19. La fabricación de un ataúd económico se hace en cadena y sirve para este recorrido fotográfico por el oficio de los trabajadores que reportan más ganancias, pero también días de trabajo más pesados y extensos. La muerte de siempre se junta con la abundante muerte de la pandemia. Los carpinteros de los muertos son también personal en primera línea desde que el contagio masivo inició. Algunos de sus familiares han muerto y han sido enterrados bajo las normas a las que la enfermedad obliga. Mientras la economía abre este lunes 24 de agosto, a falta de acuerdo entre el Ejecutivo y el Legislativo, los carpinteros de Perulapán siguen tallando ataúdes, hasta por 12 horas cada día. @elfaronet #ElSalvador #covid_19 #pandemic #desigualdad #inequality #photojournalism #centralamerica

node.text:
Presiden Direktur CIMB Niaga Tigor M. Siahaan memperlihatkan plakat penghargaan dari The Asian Banker dalam acara ‘Excellence in Retail Financial Services International Awards Ceremony’ yang digelar secara virtual, Selasa, (25/8/2020). ⁣
⁣
CIMB Niaga meraih penghargaan ‘The Most Helpful Bank during COVID-19 in Indonesia’ dari The Asian Banker karena dinilai sebagai bank yang paling peduli dan memiliki perhatian besar untuk membantu nasabah (helpful) di tengah pandemi COVID-19. ⁣
⁣
Beragam inisiatif dilakukan CIMB Niaga  untuk menjawab tantangan selama pandemi, diantaranya menyempurnakan platform perbankan digital, seperti OCTO Mobile dan OCTO Clicks, serta menggagas gerakan sosial SolidLawanCovid yang bertujuan membantu masyarakat terdampak pandemi serta mendukung perjuangan para tenaga medis.⁣
⁣
#TrijayaUpdate #CIMBNiaga #Covid19 #News #Pandemic

node.text: Enjoy! Just came Back! Back country is the best! 🌟
Enjoy! Just came Back! Back country is the best! 🌟

Later Skaters!
This Mama is outta here 🤪

Another glorious 4 day trip into #AlgonquinPark and this time I finally get to share it with @d_bow_13

I'm so excited to share with him, my love for backcountry adventures and every single resilience building challenge that comes with #SurThriving them.

This will be the first of many more adventures we take together, and I hope the start of a lifetime of epic wandering for him.

Thank you pandemic for slowing down the intensity of his sports schedule long enough to let me inspire him with something new.

#pandemic #lovegift

Anonymous Beauty🕳
.
[ MEMOIR IN JULY ]
.
/Experimental face mask design - Convertible look/ 
/ Able to be used as face mask, also could be transformed into full-face cover look/ 
.....
The story behind: 
The flowers grow like flames on a small mountain near where I live, in summer.
They are full of life. 
Starring at those ordinary creatures, I realized what has not changed since the pandemic. That is hope. 
I created a monochromatic floral hand embroidery on the mask to represent the organic presence of those flowers I seen that day.
_
Yesterday, today and forever. 
-

node.text:
My visit to South Bronx started at a bustling corner on 170th Street and Jerome Avenue, where people poured into the congested street from the subway station. Following all the beautiful street art, I eventually found a lot of young residents playing under the blazing sun inside a playground, watched over by an athletic coach and a staff of New Settlement, a nonprofit organization. Manny and Shirelle helped me convince the kids to take a break from their fun activities to model for #masktogetheramerica. I wouldn’t call this a tough shoot, but I got quite emotional. The children’s questioning eyes stay with me. Kids don’t hold back. They see what’s happening in the world. My camera is like a window for their feelings to come out.

#masktogetheramerica is about us, all of us, no matter what you do for a living or where you live in America. To end this pandemic, we will need to band together to protect our communities.

node.text:
Part 6 of my essay on the future of Maryland’s watermen. // for @chesbayprogram 

Captions:

1. Workers operating under the H-2B visa program have their temperature checked before picking crab at Russel Hall Seafood in Fishing Creek. Covid-19 has forced seafood businesses to adapt to new social distancing and health protocols. 

2. Blue crabs are pulled out of an industrial steamer at Russell Hall Seafood. Each crab will be hand-picked before being shipped and sold as lump crab meat. Sponge crabs—female crabs that are carrying unhatched eggs—are only legal to harvest in Virginia. Each sponge may contain anywhere from 750,000 to 8 million eggs, with the average sponge containing 2 million already fertilized and developing crabs. 

3. Workers pick crabs at Russell Hall Seafood. Russell Hall is one of only two out of the five picking houses on Hoopers Island that were awarded visas for workers this year. Mark Phillips, son of Russel Hall owner Harry Phillips, says “it doesn’t just hurt his business, but the whole community,” as watermen have fewer places to offload their catch. “We’ve had job fairs everywhere, Baltimore to Washington, people just aren’t going to do it,” Phillips said. “If I had to run this business and rely on Americans, I’d sell it today.” 

4. A painted fishing boat in Tilghman Island voices its owner’s support for President Trump, whose administration has acted to reduce the number of visas available to seafood processors. Watermen are predominantly conservative and Trump flags fly from many workboats. 

5. American Flags rest inside the shuttered Phillips Packing Company in Cambridge. The plant was once the largest employer in Dorchester county. Today the property is the focus of a restoration and revitalization effort by the Eastern Shore Land Conservancy.

.

node.text:
Tennis From Cincinnati  New York • Jo Konta Looks Impressive As All Around Her Look Frail - By Alix Ramsay

Covering tournaments remotely is a strange experience. Normally, at this time of year, my British colleagues and I would be either on our way to – or already in – New York for the start of the US Open.

Instead, we find ourselves stuck at home and watching the relocated Cincinnati event on TV as it is played out in Queens, NY. We are all suffering the usual jetlag (the five-hour time difference means that you are starting you working day at 4pm at the earliest and who knows when you will finish) but none of us are having the fun of being in the Big Apple.

In normal times in NY, you can get on the bus at 3am, get back to the city at 3.30am (3.15am if the driver puts his foot down – as he often does at that time of night) and always find a bar to go to, a diner to eat at, a place to chill and relax…happy days.

When you are stuck in Ramsay Towers in Weybridge, you watch a match finish at gone midnight (with the headphones, natch, in so as not to disturb the neighbours) and once the presser is over an hour later, you kick back, look at your watch and think ‘rats, I’ve nothing in the fridge, I’ve run out of tonic and the electrician is coming here at 8am to fix the shower…’ It is not particularly glamourous. Added to which, the neighbours think I’m some sort of vampiric weirdo.

But watching an American tournament on British TV (albeit streamed TV) gives a whole new view of the event. When you are there, there is an ebb and flow to every day. You wake up when the players wake up (well, may be an hour or so later); you live in their time zone. Not now.

To read more go to 10sBalls.com or tap the link in our bio ☝️.

Collage con pinturas sobre papel 
2020

En este día gris, un poco de color y naturaleza para levantar.
Este trabajo lo fui haciendo lentamente, pinte, guarde, volví a ver, corte, volví a hacer hojas, y este es el resultado.
Ame conectarme desde otro lugar con la pintura y empezar a implementar el collage con imágenes que habían producido mis manos.

#Cuantos procesos se dan a la vez, con idas y vueltas en el hacer con el trabajo manual, y en todos los procesos en general, no?

node.text:
US testing has been erratic since the start of the pandemic, shooting up and down every week. But there are some good news:⠀
⠀
The big labs, Quest Diagnostics & LabCorp announced their testing times have fallen from over a week to 1-3 days, which allows people to get their results while still contagious and can better stop spreading the infection. ⠀
⠀
To learn more good news, as well as the current numbers and stats about COVID-19 in the US and around the world, watch our August 21st Corona Health Update video on Averpoint or on IGTV! ⠀
